TY  - JOUR
T1  - Layoff Announcements and Stockholder Wealth
AU  - Worrell, Dan L.
AU  - Davidson, Wallace N.
AU  - Sharma, Varinder M.
Y1  - 1991/09/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256410
DO  - 10.5465/256410
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 662
EP  - 678
VL  - 34
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Researchers have largely ignored the strategic implications of layoffs. With the passage of the Worker Adjustment and Retraining Notification Act, many managers are anguishing about the consequences of layoff announcements for their firms and shareholders. We tested the reaction of the securities' market to announcements of 194 layoffs. Investors reacted negatively to announcements attributable to financial reasons. Negative preannouncement reactions occurred when negative hints about firms preceded announcements, and announcements of large or permanent layoffs elicited stronger negative responses than other announcements.
AB  - Researchers have largely ignored the strategic implications of layoffs. With the passage of the Worker Adjustment and Retraining Notification Act, many managers are anguishing about the consequences of layoff announcements for their firms and shareholders. We tested the reaction of the securities' market to announcements of 194 layoffs. Investors reacted negatively to announcements attributable to financial reasons. Negative preannouncement reactions occurred when negative hints about firms preceded announcements, and announcements of large or permanent layoffs elicited stronger negative responses than other announcements.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256410
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256410
